# Infisical CLI — iPix secret management

**SSOT for secrets:** [Infisical](https://infisical.com) project linked via `.infisical.json` (safe to commit).  
**Skill hub:** `.claude/skills/infisical/SKILL.md` · Docs: [CLI usage](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/usage) · [Commands](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/commands) · [Project config](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/project-config)

## Golden rules

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| Prefix secret-dependent commands with `infisical run --` | Paste API keys/tokens in chat, commits, or docs |
| `infisical login` once per machine (keyring stores session) | Commit `.env.local` — gitignored; worktree copy only |
| Store `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN`, Supabase keys in Infisical | Put shell commands at the bottom of `.env.local` (breaks MCP stdio bridges) |
| Use `--env=dev` when `.infisical.json` has no `defaultEnvironment` | `source .env.local` in agent shell commands when `infisical run` works |

## Project link

Repo root `.infisical.json`:

```json
{
  "workspaceId": "81f93e92-167a-4ae2-806e-4b5bee28cf12",
  "defaultEnvironment": "",
  "gitBranchToEnvironmentMapping": null
}
```

Because `defaultEnvironment` is empty, **always pass `--env=dev`** (or `staging` / `prod`) unless the user specifies otherwise.

Optional improvement (human sets in Infisical UI + json):

```json
"defaultEnvironment": "dev",
"gitBranchToEnvironmentMapping": { "main": "prod", "ipi/*": "dev" }
```

## Auth (one-time per machine)

```bash
# Browser login (default)
infisical login

# WSL / headless / SSH — no browser
infisical login -i

# CI / machine identity
export INFISICAL_TOKEN=$(infisical login --method=universal-auth \
  --client-id=... --client-secret=... --silent --plain)
```

EU / self-hosted: set `INFISICAL_DOMAIN` or `domain` in `.infisical.json` ([project config](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/project-config)).

## iPix command patterns

Wrap any command that needs secrets:

```bash
# Operator app (canonical) — from app/
cd app && infisical run --env=dev -- npm run dev

# Supabase verify / push (remote-only policy)
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify-rls
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:push

# Linear scripts (need LINEAR_API_KEY etc.)
infisical run --env=dev -- node scripts/linear-update-issue.mjs IPI-NNN

# Wrangler / Cloudflare
infisical run --env=dev -- npx wrangler whoami

# Tests that hit real APIs
cd app && infisical run --env=dev -- npm test
```

## Secret paths in Infisical

Use folder paths when secrets are grouped (adjust to match your Infisical layout):

```bash
infisical run --env=dev --path=/app -- npm run dev
infisical run --env=dev --path=/supabase -- npm run supabase:verify
```

List what's configured:

```bash
infisical secrets --env=dev
infisical secrets get GEMINI_API_KEY CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN --env=dev
```

Set / rotate (never echo values in terminal output to user):

```bash
infisical secrets set CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=... --env=dev
infisical secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY=... --env=dev
```

## `.env.local` vs Infisical

| Surface | Role |
|---------|------|
| **Infisical** | Canonical store for all team secrets |
| **`app/.env.local`** | Local cache for tools that read files directly (MCP `cf-mcp-bridge.sh`, Next.js, worktrees via `.worktreeinclude`) |

After rotating a secret in Infisical, sync to `app/.env.local` for file-based tools:

```bash
# Export only what you need (do not commit)
infisical export --env=dev --format=dotenv --path=/app >> app/.env.local
```

Or set keys manually in `.env.local` after updating Infisical — keep both in sync.

## Agent workflow

1. **Need a secret?** → `infisical secrets get <KEY> --env=dev` (do not print full values in replies).
2. **Run dev server / tests / verify** → `infisical run --env=dev -- <command>`.
3. **User pasted a token in chat** → tell them to rotate in Infisical + Cloudflare/provider dashboard.
4. **CI** → machine identity + `INFISICAL_TOKEN`, not user login ([usage docs](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/usage)).

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `You must be logged in` | `infisical login` or `infisical login -i` |
| Wrong secrets loaded | Add `--env=dev` explicitly |
| `infisical: command not found` | CLI installed — check `PATH` or reinstall per [CLI usage](https://infisical.com/docs/cli/usage) |
| MCP bridge can't find token | `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` must be in `app/.env.local` (sync from Infisical) |
| Domain / EU errors | `export INFISICAL_DOMAIN=https://eu.infisical.com` |
